.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="670633474014466AFF6E85EEEB70B13B" blockId="12.[163,779,197,342]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">
*The status of 
<taxonomicName id="A0B948C44014466AFEA685EDEB28B0B6" box="[371,533,198,219]" class="Malacostraca" family="Haustoriidae" genus="Haustorius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis id="55CDEF554014466AFEA685EDEB28B0B6" box="[371,533,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">H. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unclear. If a true 
<taxonomicName id="A0B948C44014466AFF7685CFE81FB094" authorityName="Muller" authorityYear="1775" box="[163,290,228,249]" class="Malacostraca" family="Haustoriidae" genus="Haustorius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="55CDEF554014466AFF7685CFE81FB094" box="[163,290,228,249]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">Haustorius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in our definition above), it would represent the only 
<taxonomicName id="A0B948C44014466AFEDB8428E8AEB175" authorityName="Muller" authorityYear="1775" box="[270,403,259,280]" class="Malacostraca" family="Haustoriidae" genus="Haustorius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="55CDEF554014466AFEDB8428E8AEB175" box="[270,403,259,280]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">Haustorius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the GoM. However, we have been unable to obtain specimens of this species and have not located it at its 
<typeStatus id="B8028DE54014466AFE68846BE8D3B138" box="[445,494,320,341]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="670633474014466AFF768454E868B1DE" blockId="12.[163,778,382,435]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">
<emphasis id="55CDEF554014466AFF768454E9CEB1F9" box="[163,243,383,404]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1264">Range:</emphasis>
Restricted to open coasts in the Atlantic and Mediterranean.
</paragraph>
